    sumArray[count]=sum;
    System.out.println();
    columnIncrement++;
    if(columnIncrement==(arr.length/2)+1) {
        rowIncrement++;
        columnIncrement=0;
    }
    if(rowIncrement&lt;(arr.length/2)+1) {
        count++;
        hourglassSumHelper(arr); // Make sure you change the recursive call as well
    }
} 
```
Then make `hourglassSum()` a wrapper function whose only purpose is to call the helper method, then print out the result:
```
static void hourglassSum(int[][] arr) {
